adjectives.description: awash (comparative more awash, superlative most awash)

entries.meaning: Washed by the waves or tide (of a rock or strip of shore, or of an anchor, etc., when flush with the surface of the water, so that the waves break over it); covered with water.
examples: The former rock is awash at low water  […]

entries.meaning: (by extension) Covered, overspread (with or in something).
examples: The Valley landscape was more awash with greenery some 11,000 years ago.
